parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: especially when slowing down to a near stop
the check engine light is not on
no error codes are present in the computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake vibration can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates when the brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle is subject to a recall
but the parts are not available
the dealer is aware of the issue
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents, putting drivers, passengers, and others at risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling Due to Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine without warning can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle may experience difficulty restarting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and complete fogging of the windshield and windows can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in low-visibility conditions such as rain or snow.
symptoms: Windshield and windows fog up immediately
requiring frequent stops to open windows and use the blower to clear the fog

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the climate control system, which requires the use of air conditioning to prevent fogging, can lead to reduced fuel efficiency, increased fuel costs, and potential warranty issues.
symptoms: Need to run the air conditioning constantly
resulting in low MPG and increased fuel consumption
and potential warranty issues if modifications are made to correct the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Component Failure (Valve Cover Gasket Leak)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A valve cover gasket leak can cause oil to leak onto the engine, potentially leading to engine failure, stalling, or even a fire, which can increase the risk of an accident or injury.
